# IFC / openBIM Standards

Reference: https://github.com/buildingsmart-community and https://standards.buildingsmart.org/

## Supported IFC Schemas

Must support these schemas (per buildingSMART certification):
- **IFC2x3** — legacy, widely used
- **IFC4** (4.0.2.1) — current standard
- **IFC4x3** (IFC4X3_ADD2) — infrastructure extensions (rail, road, bridge)

## Key IFC Concepts

- **GlobalId** (GUID): 22-char base64 identifier, unique across models
- **ExpressID**: Integer, local to a single IFC file (not portable)
- **IfcBuildingStorey**: Spatial structure for floor-based classification
- **IfcRelContainedInSpatialStructure**: Links elements to storeys
- **IfcRelDefinesByProperties**: Links property sets to elements

## GUID ↔ ExpressID Bridge

Dashboard uses ExpressID (from backend parser). 3D viewer uses GUIDs (That Open's ModelIdMap).
Always maintain a `guidToExpress` map when bridging dashboard ↔ viewer:

```javascript
const guidToExpress = new Map();
for (const el of dashboardData.elements) {
  if (el.id) guidToExpress.set(el.id, el.expressId);
}
```

## Testing

Test with official buildingSMART files from `TestIFC/`:
- Architecture, Structural, Infrastructure (Road, Rail)
- Multiple schemas (IFC4, IFC4x3)
